added.title: Beast Boy on a Shelf
added.description: Santa Claus forces Beast Boy to become a spy and report on the Titans' naughty behavior.

added.title: Christmas Crusaders
added.description: Santa Claus and Robin must stop the nefarious Coal Miner.

added.title: Collect Them All
added.description: After the other Titans are turned into collectibles and disappear, Robin must search yard sales and stores to find them.

added.title: Together Alone
added.description: Steven throws a party to bring his family together.

added.title: Escapism
added.description: Steven uses his psychic powers to find help.

added.title: Change Your Mind
added.description: Steven faces his biggest challenge yet.

added.title: The Future
added.description: Gumball, Darwin and Banana Joe investigate Banana Barbara's mysterious disappearance and uncover an old rival's shadowy scheme in the process.

added.title: The Fuss
added.description: Nicole tries, and fails, to hide her disappointment when Richard and the kids fail to remember her special day. Richard has to figure out what special day he has actually forgotten and then make it a day to remember or else!

added.title: The Gift
added.description: After they receive an extravagant invitation to Masami's birthday party, Gumball and Darwin are anxious to find just the right gift for her. However, they're not the only ones: it turns out every kid in Elmore is competing to get Masami the perfect present.

added.title: The Fury
added.description: When an unknown figure shows up and insults their Mom, the kids are expecting a massive showdown but are surprised when Mom chooses the path of peace. Mom explains Yuki, Masami's mother, is an old school friend and repeatedly refuses to fight her, despite further provocation. However when Yuki threatens to get Mom fired from her job, Mom has no choice but to partake in a rematch of a karate match her and Yuki had fought as children.

added.title: The GI
added.description: Gumball and Darwin's martial arts costumes make them a laughing stock at school.

added.title: Little Graduation
added.description: Steven and the Gems celebrate Little Homeschool's first graduating class.

added.title: Prickly Pair
added.description: After leaving Little Homeschool, Steven has found a new hobby, plants.

added.title: The Grid Car
added.description: Tulip, a headstrong 13-year-old girl, finds a mysterious train where every car contains its own universe.

added.title: The Beach Car
added.description: Tulip strikes a deal with a cat in an attempt to get home, but is the price worth it?

added.title: The Corgi Car
added.description: Tulip and One-One explore a car full of Corgis and face off against a mysterious monster.

added.title: The Crystal Car
added.description: Tulip, Atticus, and One-One enter a crystal forest car and have to take part in a musical ritual.

added.title: The Cat's Car
added.description: Tulip has to face her past.

added.title: Folk Art Foes
added.description: When Vic accidently unleashes the lord of mischief from an ancient relic, V and V have to work together to trap it back inside.

added.title: Dead Ringer
added.description: When Vic doesn't pick Val for his soccer team, Val vows to win with his own squad. But when his team doesn't match up, he resorts to supernatural means to win.

added.title: Brotherly Love
added.description: After breaking Chata's plant, Vic and Val must accomplish the seemingly easy task of replacing it; this proves difficult when their squabbling puts Monte Macabre in jeopardy.

added.title: Chata's Quinta Quinceañera
added.description: Vic and Val want to go to a friend's pool party on the same day as their grandma's quinceañera, so they use a magical flute that allows them to teleport and attend both at the same time.

added.title: Legend of the Hidden Skate Park
added.description: While searching for a hidden skate park, V and V happen upon a tribe of wild kids, who live in a society without rules or adults.

added.title: Cleaning Day
added.description: Victor & Valentino gain a newfound respect for cleanliness after Chata's house traps them inside its labyrinth of ancient, magical walls.

added.title: The Babysitter
added.description: Vic & Val want to sneak out to a secret fireworks show but are thwarted when their new babysitter, Xochi, outsmarts them at every turn.

added.title: Hurricane Chata
added.description: When V & V discover that Chata's emotions control the water in the lake, they use it to their advantage and start their own wave pool business.

added.title: Lonely Haunts Club
added.description: Instead of celebrating Valentine's Day, Vic & Val take on a dare to explore a haunted mansion with their rivals, Charlene & Pineapple.

added.title: Suerte
added.description: When Vic cheats on an enchanted board game, the malevolent characters come to life, and it's up to V & V to figure out how to put them back in the game.

added.title: Out to Launch
added.description: While on a visit to Cape Canaveral, the Tennyson Trio are present for the inaugural launch of an experimental space plane. When Vilgax commandeers the ship, Ben must stop the baddie from weaponizing the shuttle before the countdown hits zero.

added.title: Battle at Biggie Box
added.description: Ben and Billy Billions go head to head over a Sumo Slammer Set sold exclusively inside the world's largest shopping center, only to find six-year-old Simon Sez has gotten it first! A battle royal ensues inside a store that seemingly has everything except an easy to find exit.

added.title: Bon Voyage
added.description: Aboard the SS Pettigrew on its final voyage, Ben must not only battle seasickness but Steam Smythe, who looks to use his mechanical creatures to sink the steamship's modern replacement and the passengers with it!

added.title: Mayhem in Mascot
added.description: After their attempt to get a photo with every storefront mascot is foiled, Ben and Gwen sneak out at night to get their photo with the wooden bear totem known as "Yawk", only to find he and the other mascots have come to life!

added.title: Screamcatcher
added.description: When a cavity forces Ben to the dentist his day gets even worse when the malevolent magician Hex uses a nearby dream catcher to bring our hero's fears to life and transports them both to a nightmarish dreamscape.

added.title: Memories of Bobby
added.description: When a pillar of the Creek community leaves, our trio mourns their loss by remembering the good times.

added.title: Jacob of the Creek
added.description: A terrible haircut forces Craig to go undercover at the Creek.

added.title: The Climb
added.description: Craig's phone gets stuck in Mt. Sycamore, the tallest tree in the creek!

added.title: Big Pinchy
added.description: JP leads his friends on a voyage to find the biggest crayfish in the creek.

added.title: The Kid From 3030
added.description: The kids meet a mysterious kid from the future and try to help him complete his mission.

added.title: Dia de limpieza
added.description: Victor y Valentino adquieren un nuevo respeto por la limpieza después de que la casa de Chata los atrapa dentro de su laberinto de paredes antiguas y mágicas.

added.title: La ninera
added.description: Vic y Val quieren colarse en un espectáculo secreto de fuegos artificiales, pero su plan se ve frustrado cuando su nueva niñera, Xochi, los supera en todo momento.

added.title: Huracan Chata
added.description: Cuando V y V descubren que las emociones de Chata controlan el agua del lago, deciden sacar ventaja y comienzan su propio negocio de piscinas de olas.

added.title: Loteria
added.description: Cuando Vic hace trampa en un juego de mesa encantado, los malvados personajes cobran vida, y V y V son los responsables de averiguar cómo volver a ponerlos en el juego.

added.title: El club de los solitarios
added.description: En lugar de celebrar el Día de San Valentín, Vic y Val se atreven a explorar una mansión encantada con sus rivales, Charlene y Piña.

added.title: Red Action to the Future
added.description: When Red Action is called to the future for an epic battle, Enid is unsure of what to do.

added.title: Special Delivery
added.description: Enid and Rad go on a road trip to deliver a package.

added.title: Bittersweet Rivals
added.description: Enid is forced to confront lingering issues from a past friendship.

added.title: My Dad Can Beat up Your Dad
added.description: When a bully says his dad can beat up KO's mom, KO gladly accepts the challenge on Carol's behalf.

added.title: You Are Rad
added.description: When KO forgets his name tag, Rad lets him use his, which results in everyone thinking KO is Rad, including Rad himself.

added.title: The First Day
added.description: Best friends Oscar and Hedgehog get dropped off at their first day at summer camp.

added.title: Monster Babies
added.description: Alice lures Oscar and his monster friends for a tea party, but only to turn the monsters into cute babies.

added.title: Chocolate Money Badgers
added.description: Oscar learns that he can earn merit badges that unlock prizes.

added.title: Saxophone Come Home
added.description: Oscar befriends a teenage Yeti.

added.title: Pajama Pajimjams
added.description: Oscar pretends to be a talking pair of pajamas named "Jimjams" to make his friend Pajamas happy.

added.title: Oscar & Hedgehog's Melody
added.description: Susie holds the annual talent show that has the rest of the campers competing to win.

added.title: Feeling Spacey
added.description: Oscar and Hedgehog arrive on a planet that has no emotions.

added.title: Ghost the Boy
added.description: Oscar and Hedgehog befriend a ghost who can't remember who he is.

added.title: Computer Vampire
added.description: Oscar finds a mysterious old video game in the library.

added.title: The Basketball Liaries
added.description: With the help from Basketball, Oscar makes an impressive shot that scores him a spot on the Gold League.

added.title: The Prince Who Wanted Everything
added.description: The beautiful and sensitive Lumpy Space Prince flees his cruel parents to start a new life.

added.title: Gamers Never Say Die
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to find a rare, golden video game patch.

added.title: El Futuro
added.description: La mamá de Banana Joe puede predecir el futuro, pero no puede predecir su propia desaparición.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: The Pit
added.description: Kee-Oth the Blood Demon has kidnapped Jake, taken him back to his dimension and thrown him in a pit. If Finn wants to rescue his friend, he's going to need Lady Rainicorn's help... and a videotape that will reveal how to open the portal to Kee-Oth's messed-up dimension.

added.title: Coleccionalos todos
added.description: Después de que los otros Titanes son convertidos en figuras de colección y desaparecen, Robin debe recorrer ventas de garage y tiendas para encontrarlos.

added.title: Ben 4 Good Buddy
added.description: Out on a desert highway, a group of modern day highway pirates hijack the Rustbucket, trick it out and use it in a daring robbery. And while Ben and Gwen are at first glad to get rid of that "bucket of bolts", they come to realize the Rustbucket is "a part of the family." In the end our trio heroes get Max's beloved "ride" back and bring down these pirates once and for all.

added.title: Guy's Night
added.description: Pops wants to beat the milk challenge to prove he's one of the guys.

added.title: Goodbye and Good Riddance
added.description: Summer's over and Ben is back at school. Unable to tell anyone that's he all these cool aliens that they've heard about all summer, Ben suddenly realizes he's gone from a "hero" to a "zero", that is until Vilgax comes after him with a vengeance. Ben must now reveal his hero side to his parents and to his fellow classmates. In doing so he saves his town and teams up with his dad to destroy Vilgax once and for all. But there is some bad news...Gwen has switched schools and is in Ben's class!

added.title: Merry Moochmas
added.description: It's wintertime in Aberdale and Clarence is convinced his winter wish for snow in Arizona will come true! However, his classmate Belson along with his grumpy cousin Gary Mooch are a little tougher to convince.

added.title: Sumo Goes West
added.description: Clarence learns his best friend Sumo may transfer to another school! It's up to Clarence to protest, petition and rally to convince everyone to let Sumo stay - or face losing his closest school pal!

added.title: Fortune Cookie
added.description: Rigby swaps fortune cookie fortunes with Benson.

added.title: Clarence for President
added.description: It's school election time at Aberdale Elementary, and Jeff is once again determined to become Class President. However like previous years, he's unsuccessful in connecting with other kid. That is until he sees a shoe-in puppet President, the lovable Clarence!

added.title: Pool's Out for Summer
added.description: The boys go to the Aberdale Community Pool for a day of wet fun! While Jeff slowly wades in the shallow end, getting used to the water, Sumo tries to conquer the diving board, redeeming himself from last summer's bellyflop, and Clarence sneaks past the lifeguards into the hot tub for a boiling surprise…

added.title: The Boxcurse Children
added.description: Clarence, Jeff, and Sumo stumble upon a mysterious box. After they open it, some strange things begin to happen. Convinced they've unlocked a curse, they become determined to reverse it!

added.title: Fuzzy Dice
added.description: Everyone wants to give Pops some fuzzy dice for his birthday.

added.title: El Regreso de los Guardabosques Madreselva
added.description: Craig descubre que los Guardabosques Madreselva se han infiltrado en su lado del Arroyo para robar su posesión más preciada.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Kelsey la Anciana
added.description: Una discusión entre los Ancianos del Arroyo deja un lugar vacante en su juego de rol de mesa, así que Kelsey se une a la campaña.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Grudge Match
added.description: Ben and Kevin 11 are beamed up to a space ship where must learn to battle together in order to bring down a vicious alien fight promoter.

added.title: The Pods
added.description: Finn and Jake must sort out the good magic beans from the bad.

added.title: The Silent King
added.description: Finn and Jake get to live like royalty, but soon fine the easy life doesn't suit them. Or at least not Finn.

added.title: The Real You
added.description: Finn has to give a speech at Princess Bubblegum's Science BBQ and seeks out a quick fix to make himself smarter.

added.title: Tooth or Consequences
added.description: Blossom's fear of the dentist's drill causes her to avoid it at all costs.

added.title: Midnight at the Mayor's Mansion
added.description: When the Mayor's mansion is stalked by a vicious, ghostly monster, he calls the Powerpuff Girls for help.

added.title: Karaoke Video
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby need to get an embarrassing tape from the Karaoke bar before their friends see it.

added.title: Sugar, Spice, and Super Lice
added.description: When Buttercup gets super lice, her sisters must battle them to save her.

added.title: Rivales Agridulces
added.description: Enid se ve obligada a enfrentar temas pendientes de una amistad pasada.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Accion Roja al Futuro
added.description: Cuando convocan a Acción Roja a una batalla épica en el futuro, Enid no está segura de lo que debe hacer.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Entrega Especial
added.description: Enid y Rad salen de viaje en auto para entregar un paquete.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Tiger Trails
added.description: In the final moments of helping a kid, Uncle Grandpa just needs his trusty Giant Realistic Flying Tiger, but when he finds out she's gone, it sends UG on a journey to find the tiger and figure out why she left.

added.title: La Melancolia de Oscar y Erizo
added.description: Susie organiza el concurso anual de talentos, y todos los campistas compiten para ganar.

added.title: Dog Daze/In Focus
added.description: Dog Daze: Lightning discovers a new Bakugan, Artulean, leading to an unhealthy rivalry with Howlkor./In Focus: While Lia's newswoman mom does an expose on the AO Strata the Hunter tries to capture Hydorous.

added.title: Sintiendose Especiales
added.description: Oscar y Erizo llegan a una planeta que no tiene emociones.

added.title: The Exit/The Lost and the Cost
added.description: The Exit: The AO compete with a rival Brawling team for ViewTube hits leading to a "winner take all" brawl./The Lost and the Cost: Everett Ray, a promotor, tries to get the AO to join an official league for Bakugan Battling.

added.title: Fantasma, El Nino
added.description: Oscar y Erizo se hacen amigos de un fantasma que no recuerda quién es.

added.title: Mr. Moon/What's Wrong with Dan
added.description: Mr. Moon: Wynton finds a new Bakugan who proves difficult to control but things get more complicated when Col. Tripp seizes control of Trox./What's Wrong with Dan: With "Dan" behaving strangely toward the AO Lightning sniffs out the truth- an impostor!

added.title: Vampiro de Computadora
added.description: Oscar encuentra un videojuego viejo y misterioso en la biblioteca.

added.title: Babysitting Bedlam/Rubbed the Wrong Way
added.description: Rubbed the Wrong Way: After a Bakugan field errupts the town kids stampede to get their own Bakugan but when the field is contaminated Lia must save the day./Babysitting Bedlam: Dan and Wynton meet a strange boy who leads them into an underground maze where they discover the boy's Bakugan has been enslaved.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Ate My Homework
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa shows up and mistakenly eats a kid's Egyptian diorama for school, he helps the kid bring an actual pyramid to class, but accidentally unleashes an evil mummy on the world.

added.title: Mi Papa Puede Vencer a Tu Papa
added.description: Cuando un bravucón dice que su papá puede darle una paliza a la mamá de K.O., nuestro héroe acepta con alegría el desafío en nombre de Carol.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Cronicas de Mentiras Basquetboleras
added.description: Con la ayuda de Basketball, Oscar hace un tiro impresionante que le permite conseguir un lugar en la Liga Dorada.

added.title: Mask of Power/Story Holes
added.description:
Mask of Power: Philomena Dusk from AAAnimus Corp. hires Magnus and gives him a control implant to bolster the power of his Bakugan to defeat Dan./Story Holes:  
A cryptic call leads the AO in search of a missing Bakugan but they soon realize the call was actually a test from a mysterious benefactor.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa for a Day
added.description: When UG gets his head stuck in a peanut butter jar, Mr. Gus and Pizza Steve have to pretend to be UG and help a kid.

added.title: Tu Eres Rad
added.description: Cuando K.O. se olvida su chapa identificatoria, Rad le presta la suya, lo cual hace que todos piensen que K.O. es Rad, incluido el mismo Rad.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Treasure Map
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang don't have money to pay for their meal at a restaurant.  But when they discover a treasure map, it could be the answer to all their problems.  Too bad the treasure map is actually a restaurant activity placemat.

added.title: A escalar
added.description: iEl teléfono de Craig se atasca en el Monte Sicomoro, el árbol más alto del Arroyo!
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Don Pellizco
added.description: JP lleva a sus amigos de viaje para encontrar el cangrejo de río más grande del Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: El chico del 3030
added.description: Los niños conocen a un misterioso niño del futuro y tratan de ayudarlo a completar su misión.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: A Guilded Cage
added.description: Mega Man must stop Namagem and an army of hypnotized Good Guild bots from breaking into Dr. Light's lab.

added.title: To Air Is Robot
added.description: Air Man stakes a claim on the skies above Silicon City, threatening anything that trespasses on his airspace.

added.title: Watt's Happening?!
added.description: When Elec Man derails the school play by hijacking Silicon Central's power, Aki/Mega Man must use what he has learned onstage to defeat his supercharged foe.

added.title: Chill Out, Bruh
added.description: Aki and Suna take a rehabilitated Ice Man out for a day in the city, but things take a turn for the worse as he misinterprets their cues and turns a game of hover hockey into a literal freeze out!

added.title: Big Bad Dreams
added.description: When Namagem starts using his Hypno powers to haunt Aki's dreams, our hero must face his fears in the dreamscape.

added.title: Electric Buttercup
added.description: Buttercup gets more than she bargained for when she makes a deal with a cool '80s metalhead to get a sweet new guitar.

added.title: Poorbucks
added.description: When Morbucks loses her money, Blossom tries to reform her.

added.title: Max's Monster
added.description: Grandpa Max's old Plumber partner, Phil, seeks Max's help to tame the monster within. (Introducing new Ben alien, Buzzshock; Re-introducing old Ben alien, Benvicktor.)

added.title: Mystery, Incorporeal
added.description: An old enemy emerges while Ben and Rook visit Kevin and Gwen at college.

added.title: It's a Mad, Mad, Mad Ben World Part 1
Let's Do the Time War Again
added.description: Ben, Skurd and Rook find themselves caught in an endless time loop as enemies from the future converge on Bellwood.

added.title: Malgax Attacks
added.description: Ben finally manages to rid himself of Skurd... just when he needs the Slime-Biot most.

added.title: Origin of Species
added.description: Origin of Species, Part 1: Dan meets his partner Bakugan Drago for the first time and we learn about the incident that happened on Earth twelve years ago./Origin of Species, Part 2: Dan and friends win the Bakugan Battle, firmly establishing the Awesome Ones as our heroes and Bakugan Brawlers.

added.title: Burger Run/Monkey See, Monkey Don't
added.description: Burger Run: When the local Burger Joint is being threatened by a rogue Bakugan, Dan steps up to save the day and the burgers!/Monkey See, Monkey Don't: The AO stop neighborhood kids from copycat behavior (namely, using their Bakugan for frivolous reasons).

added.title: Bully for You/Trolling for Laughs
added.description: Bully for You: The AO must handle a neighborhood bully who is using his Bakugan to pick on the local kids./Trolling for Laughs: Wynton's constant practical jokes wear thin on his Bakugan Trox so the Bakugan decide to teach him a lesson.

added.title: Local Heroes/Pegatrix
added.description: Local Heroes: After the AO cause accidental destruction Dan's parents question whether the kids should be allowed to keep their Bakugan./Pegatrix: Lia disagrees with her new Bakugan Pegatrix on battle techniques but during a fierce fight Lia must rely on Pegatrix's battle savy.

added.title: Frenemies/Strata's Fear
added.description: Frenemies: Two new Bakugan Brawlers, Shun and Magnus, try out for the AO./Strata's Fear: The AO solve the mystery of a kid's missing Bakugan and meet a Bakugan Hunter named Strata.

added.title: Swish
added.description: Namagem attacks Mega Man using a variety of powers, revealing that they both can replicate schematics. However, Namagem can carry more than three at a time! The true beginning of the mysterious villain's arc begins here.

added.title: Minus Mini
added.description: When Mega Mini is kidnapped by Blasto Woman, Mega Man must track down his missing partner without the full use of his own systems.

added.title: A Cut Above
added.description: Aki and Bert accidentally damage a bonsai tree outside the Lighthouse, sending the Lights' perfectionist gardener on a slicing-and-dicing spree as Cut Man.

added.title: A Bot and His Dog
added.description: Tired of fielding of low stakes house calls, Mega Man gets what he wishes for when Hypno Woman hijacks the local power plant.

added.title: This Man, This Man Man!
added.description: When Guts Man goes on a ravenous rampage across the city, Mega Man must turn to an unlikely ally, Man Man, a bumbling DIY human analog to our hero.

added.title: Divided We Stand
added.description: While at the beach, Ben discovers a new hero, Ditto, and soon has the ability to create multiple Dittos at once. These multiple Dittos can't agree on anything and drive Gwen crazy. However when the chips are down, these Dittos come together as one fighting force in order to defeat Animo and his army of replicant Stinkflies.

added.title: Game Over
added.description: When Ben, as Upgrade, and Gwen get zapped into a Sumo Slammers video game, Ben soon has to deal with Gwen's superior gaming skills, while he also tries to impress his video icon in the game.

added.title: Camp Fear
added.description: When a race of alien mushrooms takes over a summer camp, Ben discovers a whole new alien to battle the menace.

added.title: Problemas Dentales
added.description: A Puppycorn se le cae su primer diente, y Unikitty está emocionada por su hermanito, ique ahora recibirá la visita de la legendaria Hada de los Dientes! Pero cuando el Hada de los Dientes no aparece, Unikitty y sus amigos asumen la responsabilidad. ¿Acaso se meterán demasiado rápido y con demasiada soltura con los dientes sueltos y tocarán un nervio sensible?

added.title: Viaje en Carretera
added.description: Richard decidió llevar a Unikitty y a la banda a un agradable y relajante viaje de 10 horas por la carretera. Al principio todo el mundo está en contra del viaje, pero pronto empiezan a divertirse. Por desgracia, su idea de diversión no es la de Richard. Pronto, el conductor comienza a sucumbir ante su furia interior al volante. Para colmo de males, los persigue un semirremolque asesino, y su coche ha sido invadido por un extraño autoestopista. ¿Richard perderá la razón o el viaje será un gran éxito?

added.title: Dia de elecciones
added.description: En un esfuerzo por demostrarle a Master Frown que no es una tirana, Unikitty acuerda celebrar una elección para ver quién será la nueva princesa del Unireino. En una situación sorpresiva, Master Frown toma una ventaja temprana en las encuestas. Unikitty descubre que Frown gana porque está haciendo trampa. ¿Recurrirá Unikitty a sus propios trucos sucios para ganar las elecciones o permanecerá fiel a sí misma y seguirá tratando de ganar gracias a su amabilidad?

added.title: Campamento Unikitty
added.description: La pandilla está lista para un fin de semana increíble, para vivir la buena vida acampando con estilo en la divertida y amigable naturaleza. Pero cuando Halcondrilo desafía su idea de acampar (debería ser una lucha por la supervivencia en los bosques hostiles), la pandilla intercambia el lugar con él: ahora, Halcondrilo vive una vida de campamento glamoroso mientras Unikitty y los otros sobreviven en la naturaleza. ¿Seguirá creyendo Unikitty que la "increíble naturaleza" es tan increíble si encuentran su destrucción por causas naturales?

added.title: Quien se llevo a Pan
added.description: Cuando Pan desaparece de la fiesta de Unikitty, ila princesa lidera una búsqueda para encontrarlo y desenmascarar al secuestrador de tostadas!

added.title: El Origen de las Especies Parte 1
added.description: Dan conoce a su pareja Bakugan, Drago, por primera vez y nos enteramos del "incidente" que ocurrió en la Tierra hace doce años.

added.title: El Origen de las Especies Parte 2
added.description: Dan y sus amigos ganan la Batalla Bakugan, demostrando que los Fantásticos son nuestros héroes y los mejores Peleadores Bakugan.

added.title: Un almuerzo inesperado
added.description: Cuando el Restaurante de Hamburguesas es amenazado por un violento Bakugan, Dan llega para salvar el día...y las hamburguesas.

added.title: Una leccion para todos
added.description: Los Fantásticos le enseñan a unos chicos del vecindario a no imitar a los demás. Por ejemplo, a quienes utilizan a sus Bakugan con fines frívolos.

added.title: El bravucon
added.description: Los Fantásticos deben lidiar con un bravucón que usa a su Bakugan para intimidar a los chicos del vecindario.

added.title: Bromas pesadas
added.description: Las constantes bromas pesadas de Wynton colman la paciencia de su Bakugan, Trox, quien decide darle una lección.

added.title: Heroes locales
added.description: Los Fantásticos provocan una ola de destrucción por accidente, y los padres de Dan se preguntan si deberían permitirle a los niños conservar sus Bakugan.

added.title: Pegatrix
added.description: Lia no concuerda con las técnicas de Pegatrix, pero durante una intensa batalla, debe aprender a confiar en los conocimientos de su Bakugan.

added.title: Ene-amigos
added.description: Dos nuevos Peleadores Bakugan, Shun y Magnus, buscan ser parte de Los Fantásticos.

added.title: El miedo de Strata
added.description: Los Fantásticos resuelven la misteriosa desaparición del Bakugan de un niño, y conocen a un cazador de Bakugan llamado Strata.

added.title: Huyendo de casa
added.description: Descubriremos el misterioso pasado de Shun, su relación con su padre (un magnate de la industria), y su deseo por tener una familia más unida.

added.title: Un verdadero lider
added.description: Entre diversas amenazas, como el misterioso Shargo Ronin, Dan y Shun no pueden acordar la mejor forma de convertir a Los Fantásticos en un verdadero equipo.

added.title: Pesadilla de verano
added.description: Drago y los otros Bakugan de Los Fantásticos se enfrentan a una nueva y poderosa amenaza, solo para dejarlos preguntándose si todo habrá sido un sueño.

added.title: Padres y amigos
added.description: Osamu Kazami viene para llevarse a su hijo Shun a casa y se encuentra con un obstáculo que no había contemplado.

added.title: Industrias Dusk Parte 1
added.description: Los Fantásticos conocen a Benton Dusk y descubren que su pequeño mundo está a punto de volverse mucho más grande.

added.title: Industrias Dusk Parte 2
added.description: Benton Dusk revela que Los Fantásticos son considerados personas de interés por poderosas corporaciones como AAAnimus.

added.title: Stratificados
added.description: Los Fantásticos emprenden una misión en el misterioso mundo laberíntico de Vestroia para buscar a Strata El Cazador y liberar a los Bakugan que tiene presos.

added.title: Aventura en el laberinto
added.description: Perdidos en el laberinto de Vestroia, Los Fantásticos se enfrentan a poderosas fuerzas que parecen luchar por el control del planeta.

added.title: Atrapados en la jungla
added.description: Aún perdidos en Vestroia, Los Fantásticos experimentan los efectos de la Célula Núcleo que altera sus cuerpos, y se encuentran cara a cara con el monstruo Bakugan, Tiko.

added.title: Sabro Atraco
added.description: Richard preparó uno de los postres más sabrosos de todos los tiempos, pero lo cerró con llave hasta que los amigos terminen su cena aburrida. Esto no va a seguir así. Para organizar un atraco, Unikitty organiza a sus amigos como un comité de expertos para entrar, salir y comer ese sabroso bocadillo sin que Richard lo sepa. Pero este atraco tiene un traspié. ¿Podrán los amigos llevarse el pastel?

added.title: Demonios internos
added.description: Los Fantásticos encuentran la forma de salir de Vestroia, pero descubren que en realidad están en un mundo paralelo.

added.title: Una extrana conexion
added.description: Drago lidera a los Bakugan contra la amenaza de Tiko, para proteger una poderosa fuente de energía.

added.title: Dia de Playa
added.description: Unikitty y la pandilla se preparan para un día divertido en la playa, pero cuando Master Frown aparece como socorrista para arruinar sus planes en la arena, Unikitty y la pandilla se embarcan en una búsqueda para encontrar el legendario lugar perfecto, lejos del dominio tiránico de Frown. Pero ¿podrán llegar allí antes de que Frown lo reclame para él o su búsqueda se convertirá en un verdadero fastidio playero?

added.title: La Celula Nucleo
added.description: Los Fantásticos defienden la Célula Núcleo de un ataque de Tiko, y en el último intento de Dan por salvarla, él y Drago logran liberar un nuevo poder.

added.title: Hogar, dulce hogar
added.description: Los Fantásticos vuelven a casa y se dan cuenta de que el tiempo no ha pasado. Pronto descubren que su conocimiento acerca de las batallas ha aumentado de forma exponencial.

added.title: Magia Tragica
added.description: Cuando Richard monta un espectáculo de magia amateur, la Dra. Fox se obsesiona por descubrir cómo se hacen esos trucos que desafían la ciencia. Pero mientras se propone usar todo su intelecto para encontrar formas experimentales de hacer los trucos que vio en la fiesta del cachorro, ¿acaso arruinará accidentalmente el asombro de la magia?

added.title: Un golpe de ternura
added.description: Después de derrotar a Strata, Los Fantásticos se dan cuenta de que no volvieron solos, sino con un Bakugan parecido a un panda que les dará muchos problemas.

added.title: Senor Casero
added.description: El propietario amenazó a Master Frown y a Brock con desalojarlos a menos que arreglen el daño que le hicieron a su apartamento. Preocupado, Brock invita a Unikitty y a la pandilla para que los ayuden. En lugar de hacer lo que los chicos quieren en su casa, Unikitty procede a hacer lo que ella quiere. Al darse cuenta de su error, devuelve el apartamento a su antiguo estado asqueroso, pero ahora Frown y Brock están en peligro de desalojo de nuevo. Deben aliarse a Unikitty y la banda para luchar contra el malvado casero y salvar su hogar.

added.title: El hijo prodigo
added.description: Mientras los Fantásticos intentan evolucionar a sus Bakugan como lo hizo Dan con Drago, el primo de Shun, Masato, llega a la ciudad para llevarlo de regreso a Japón.

added.title: El poder interior
added.description: Masato Kazami vuelve junto con los guardaespaldas de la familia para llevar a Shun a Japón, pero esta vez, Shun y Hydorous tienen una sorpresa preparada.

added.title: El baul de los recuerdos
added.description: Al ser confrontada por China Riot, Lia logra evolucionar a Pegatrix cuando comprende la verdadera razón de su obsesión por las cámaras.

added.title: Mision Espacial Peligrosa
added.description: Después de la explosión de su nave espacial, Unikitty y la banda flotan indefensos por el espacio. Mientras tratan de formular un plan que los lleve a casa a salvo, vuelven a ver qué parte de la responsabilidad por la destrucción de su nave tiene cada uno. ¿Lograrán volver a casa? Y lo que es más importante, ¿quién tendrá la culpa si no lo hacen?

added.title: Malos actores
added.description: Alguien expone a Dan por mentir acerca de la evolución de Drago, mientras el equipo se enfrenta a Duran Dane y su desdichado Bakugan, Nillious.

added.title: El atrapador
added.description: Dan y Wynton se encuentran con la posible ubicación secreta de la Célula Núcleo, y con el coronel Tripp, que busca apoderarse de la fuente de energía.

added.title: La sed de poder
added.description: Tras una discusión entre Wynton y Dan, el coronel Tripp controla la mente de Wynton para que ataque la ciudad con Lupitheon. Esto inicia una guerra entre Los Fantásticos y el ejército.

removed.title: Ace of Squares
removed.description: Craig vows to make the game of Four Square fun again by challenging its most dominant player!

removed.title: Doorway to Helen
removed.description: Craig makes a long distance connection with a kid that loves the creek as much as he does.

removed.title: The Last Kid in the Creek
removed.description: A terrible curse leaves Craig as the only kid in the creek.
